10-day Film Show Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 6 (KCNA) -- A ten-day film show opened to celebrate the 60th founding anniversary of the Workers' Party Korea.
 Documentary films and feature films will be screened in cinemas and cultural houses across the country in the period to provide the audience with an opportunity to look back on the 60-year-long history of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the films are documentaries dealing with the noble revolutionary life and undying feats of President Kim Il Sung and the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il such as "They Have Always Been Together in the Work for the People," "The Fatherly Leader among Servicepersons" and "Under the Great Brilliant Commander" (serials).
 Cinema-goers will also watch films impressively depicting the Korean people's pride and honor of enjoying a worthwhile life under the benevolent care of the Party and the true picture of the mother party looking after the destiny and future of the people including documentary "Immense Honor and Happiness of the Nation," feature films "Guarantee" (two parts) and "The Man People Wait for." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To be shown in this period are films dealing with the heroic struggle of servicepersons and people in the DPRK such as documentary "Self-reliance Is the Only Way Out" and feature film "The River Kumjin" (two parts). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An opening ceremony of the film show was held at the People's Palace of Culture Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the ceremony were Jong Ha Chol, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, Choe Ik Gyu, minister of Culture, and others.

Palestinian Ambassador Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 6 (KCNA) -- Shaher Mohammed Abdlah, Palestinian ambassador e. p. to the DPRK, hosted a reception at the embassy Wednesday evening on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 In his speech the ambassador said that with the foundation of the WPK by President Kim Il Sung a new history started in carving out the destiny of the Korean people and the Korean people have had a powerful political leadership leading the revolution and construction to victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Victory and glory are in store for the WPK which is leading the revolution and construction under the banner of the Juche idea, holding leader Kim Jong Il in high esteem, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that the revolutionary and militant ties between the peoples of the DPRK and Palestine whose foundation was laid by President Kim Il Sung and President Yasser Arafat are growing stronger under the leadership of Kim Jong Il and Mahmoud Abbas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, in his speech noted that Kim Jong Il has led the WPK in his early years, developing the party into the party of Kim Il Sung and trained all the people to be the revolutionary people remaining loyal to the idea and cause of the party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said the WPK and the Korean people invariably support the just struggle of the Palestinian people to retake their lost territory and bitterly denounce Israel's illegal moves to establish "security wall" and that the just cause of the Palestinian people will emerge victorious without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were Kim Su Hak, minister of Public Health, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Kim Thae Jong, vice-director of a department of the WPK Central Committee, Kim Hyong Jun, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and others.

Dam Project of Nyongwon Power Station Completed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nyongwon, October 5 (KCNA) -- The Nyongwon Power Station has been built in the upper reaches of the River Taedong as a gift of loyalty to the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea by Korean People's Army soldiers and builders.
 The dam of the power station is another monumental edifice of the Songun era which was built across the breadth of the river flowing in the remote mountainous region thanks to President Kim Il Sung's grand nature-harnessing plan and leader Kim Jong Il's wise guidance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A commissioning ceremony took place here on Oct. 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ceremony was attended by Premier of the DPRK Cabinet Pak Pong Ju, KPA Vice Marshal Ri Yong Mu who is vice-chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and Secretary of the WPK Central Committee Kim Ki Nam.
 A congratulatory message of the WPK Central Committee was conveyed to soldier-builders and helpers who performed great feats in the dam project.
 The message noted that the solider-builders have fully demonstrated the noble spiritual world and the invincible might of the KPA which defends the country and ensures people's happiness upholding slogan "Let us take charge of defending the country and building socialism!" They also gave great confidence and encouragement to the party members and other working people in their vigorous efforts to build a great prosperous powerful nation, it added, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK Central Committee highly praises the heroic solider-builders and helpers for completing the large dam project of the Nyongwon Power Station to present a valuable labor gift to the 60th anniversary of the glorious WPK and positively contributing to demonstrating the vitality of the great Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 KPA General Yun Jong Rin in a report said that the feats performed by soldier-builders who have devoted themselves to building the dam, glorifying their youth and happiness in the construction site will shine long in the history of building a great prosperous powerful nation and that the fatherland and the people will never forget their heroism and feats shown in building a monumental edifice of   Kim Jong Il's era through their do-or-die struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the ceremony the participants looked round the dam.

Colorful Functions Held in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 6 (KCNA) -- More colorful functions were held on Oct. 5 to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. 
 A public presentation of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces on the greatness and undying exploits of the WPK was held at the April 25 House of Culture while an art exhibition, a pencil drawing festival and a calligraphic contest of the Korean People's Army opened. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending the public presentation were Jo Myong Rok, director of the General Political Department of the Korean People's Army, Kim Yong Chun, chief of the General Staff of the KPA, Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, its leading officials and servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jo Myong Rok, Kim Il Chol and others who took the floor told the participants that over the last six decades the WPK has performed undying exploits that would shine forever in the nation's history by victoriously leading the revolutionary struggle of the Korean people for sovereignty, independence and socialism, adding that in this course the WPK has grown strong to be an experienced and tested revolutionary party and an invincible party unequivocally supported and trusted by all the people. 
 On display at the art exhibition are at least 900 successful art works including computer-aided paintings and Korean paintings created by painters and soldiers of the KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the entries to the pencil drawing festival and the calligraphic contest are at least 1,000 works done by soldiers while standing guard over the defence line of the country and by those in sites of socialist economic construction.
 Meanwhile, a Korean stamp exhibition was open in Pyongyang. 
 On display there are stamps dealing with the undying revolutionary exploits of the three generals of Mt. Paektu. Also displayed there according to themes are at least 4,000 varieties of stamps truthfully depicting the 60 year-long history of victory and glory covered by the WPK under the wise leadership of President Kim Il Sung and leader   Kim Jong Il and the proud successes achieved by the Korean people in various fields through a heroic struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A combined performance of the 16th national art festival of members of the Korean Democratic Women's Union was given at the Women's Hall.

Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition Opens
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 6 (KCNA) -- A Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia exhibition grandly opened here in celebration of the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 On display at the venue of the exhibition were at least 20,000 ported Kimilsungias and Kimjongilias presented by 85 units including armed forces organs, commissions and ministries of the cabinet and national institutions, and foreign friends and overseas compatriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the participants in the opening ceremony at the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition today were Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop, Jong Ha Chol, Kwak Pom Gi and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kang Nung Su, chairman of the Korean Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Committee, in an opening speech called for holding the exhibition on a high level so as to highly praise the undying feats of the peerlessly great men in party building and powerfully demonstrate to the world once again the single-minded unity of all the army and people who are vigorously advancing toward the future of a great prosperous powerful nation under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called upon the participants to exchange successes and experience gained in cultivating, propagating and disseminating flowers of the sun and cooperate with each other and activate the cultivation and dissemination of the flowers to meet the requirements of the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the opening ceremony the participants looked round the exhibition.

Stream of People Visit Monument to Party Founding
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 6 (KCNA) -- An increasing number of people visit the Monument to Party Founding with the approach of the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea (October 10).
 The monument, located in central part of Munsu Street of Taedonggang District, Pyongyang, was erected to convey to the rising generations the great exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung in the cause of building the Juche-oriented revolutionary party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to Ri Ok Hui, a section chief of the management office of the monument, the visitors to the monument-- servicepersons, working people from all walks of life, youth, students and schoolchildren across the country-- total more than 3,078,000 after it was unveiled on the occasion of the Party's 50th birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the last decade over 178,500 south Koreans, overseas compatriots and foreigners have also called at it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This shows the deep trust of the Korean people and world progressives in the WPK, the ever-victorious revolutionary party of Juche, founded by President Kim Il Sung and led by Kim Jong Il.
